******
[1] China (salmonellosis)
Date: Sat 8 May 2004
From: Alfonso Rodriguez <arodriguezm@SaludFMV.org>
Source: Yahoo News, UK [edited]
<http://uk.news.yahoo.com/040508/323/et3nw.html>


94 funeral guests in hospital in China with food poisoning
-----------------------------------------------
94 people, including 22 children, were in the hospital in northern China
after falling ill at a funeral dinner, probably from salmonella poisoning.

Around 160 people fell ill at the dinner on Thu evening, 6 May 2004, in the
Inner Mongolia village of Zhenghao, the Xinhua news agency said. Of those
in the hospital in the Dalad district on Sat 8 May 2004, 20 were in serious
condition with high temperatures. One of them was in a coma, Xinhua said.

Staff at the hospital said the poisoning was likely the result of eating
food contaminated with salmonella bacteria.

